# Performance mods for Forge 1.20.1

These mods directly improve modpack performance through code optimizations. 


| Name | Links | Description | Alternatives |
|------|-------|-------------| --------------|
| Alternate Current | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/alternate-current) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/alternate-current) | Vanilla-compatible redstone optimizations | - | - |
| Bobby Reforged | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/bobby-reforged) | Allows for render distances greater than the server’s view-distance setting | - | [Farsight](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/farsight), though this mod lacks a chunk caching feature. |
| Connectivity | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/connectivity) | Fix Login timeouts, Packet sizes errors, Payloads errors, ghostblocks and more | - | [Packet Fixer](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/packet-fixer) |
| Dynamic FPS | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/dynamic-fps) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/dynamic-fps) | Improve performance when Minecraft is in the background | - | [FPS Reducer](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/fps-reducer) |
| Embeddium* | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/embeddium) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/embeddium) | Rendering optimizations | - | [Xenon](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/xenon) |
| FastFurnace | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/fastfurnace) | A performance upgrade for the furnace | - | - |
| FastSuite | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/fastsuite) | A performance upgrade for the JSON recipe system | - | [Recipe Essentials](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/recipe-essentials-forge-fabric) |
| ModernFix* | [CF](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/modernfix) / [MR](https://modrinth.com/mod/modernfix) | All-in-one mod that improves performance, reduces memory usage, and fixes many bugs | Enabling [Dynamic Resources](https://github.com/embeddedt/ModernFix/wiki/Dynamic-Resources-FAQ) can halve RAM usage | - |

\* - A must-have mod for nearly any modpack. Only in very rare circumstances should you not use this mod or an equivalent.

** - Prone to issues or conflicts with other mods